Title: Zendesk Moves from DynamoDB to MySQL and S3 to Save over 80% in Costs
Description: Zendesk reduced its data storage costs by over 80% by migrating from DynamoDB to a tiered storage solution using MySQL and S3. The company considered different storage technologies and decided to combine the relational database and the object store to strike a balance between querybility and scalability while keeping the costs down.
